My most favorite Meatball Sub. Get it on a sesame roll. Ask for extra sauce. The flavorful meatballs are the star of the show but the sauce is really good and I always wish I had a little more even though it would mean a messier sandwich. Did I mention the meatballs? SO good, well seasoned and smashed/broken so you can actually take a bite of the sandwich. If you like a meatball sub smothered in melted cheese, this is not the sub for you (though I'm sure they would add cheese if you ask). This meatball sub is all about the meatballs, sauce and roll.  Everyone that works at Joe's is a delight. If you don't leave smiling, there's probably something wrong with you. If you're lucky, you might get serenaded while you wait for your order.

Rare. This is Little Italy of SF or NY brought to NY. The Arrabiatta sauce is a triumphant ecstasy of savory tomato essence with just the perfect level of spice.  Hailing from Padua, Chef Francesco and his sister/mother, drum up the freshest pasta in NY, and the no-nonsense menu and reasonable pricing make this quite the prize.  Probably the greatest contrast between excellent food and no frills that I've experienced in the city, in at least a year and a half. All of the pomp adorning typical upscale Italian restaurants is conspicuously missing.  Instead is a homemade Northern Italian experience of the highest order. I ordered the spinach ricotta ravioli with the butter sage sauce and more recently the tagliatelle with meat sauce.   Both have me in a stir.  When they begin making their lemon as well as hazelnut cookies again, you must add them to your regular order.

You can't find too many places like this anymore and it's  a shame. I can almost guarantee that you will be hard pressed to find a sandwich on par with them in all the 5 boroughs. Joe's Deli has always felt like my little secret. When other people would tell me that knew what great authentic Italian food is, I would bring some mozzarella from Joe's and blow them away. Joe's Deli is my favorite place for  an Italian hero in the entire city! I would give them 6 stars if I could. Sounds like hyperbole right... Well, I would put them up against any other deli that considers itself authentic Italian cuisine and I know they would hold their own. The meats are deliciously cured. The mozzarella is made fresh on site. They have a wide selection of food from Italy, but I love the heros so much, I have yet to try them all! When my wife got out of heart surgery the first thing I brought her to eat in the hospital was some mozzarella from Joe's because it made her smile and reminded her of her love for Italian food. Joe's staff are dedicated, attentive and you can see the pride they have in the food they prepare and sell. It's a business that has been in the neighborhood for a long time. It's the type of place that makes you feel like family when you go visit. Walking into the store makes you feel like you are taking a step back in time... to a time where everyone in the neighborhood knew each other and looked out for each other and I miss those times! Go  grab a hero at Joe's! A classic Italian New York deli!!   Try the Boccocini while your there! It will blow you away!!
